Passengers must remain hidden below deck the entire trip.
The Coast Guard can only observe how deep the ship is swimming, as there are no other signs of the crowd.
Food and drink are provided, but the less passengers defecate and vomit, the better.
After expenses, Küçük receives about 53,000 euros for one luxury cruise.
He does not take care of practical matters himself, but hires captains, recruiters, guards, lodgers and other smaller factors to do the work for him.
In the summer season, there are at least hundreds of transports and Küçük Tienaa millions.
He is believed to have bought land, a pharmaceutical company and more than a hundred apartments, which he rents out, through cover companies.
