Four people, including a four-year-old boy, were killed in southern Nepal after police fired rubber bullets into a crowd demonstrating against the country&#39;s proposed new constitution, an official said Wednesday.
The violence happened on Tuesday night in the Rupandeh district, about 175 miles west of the capital, Kathmandu.
